#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cdeveloper%5Carchitecture.md:1
msgid "Architecture"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cdeveloper%5Carchitecture.md:3
msgid ""
"The CPRMV API is a single-process FastAPI application. All logic lives in "
"`serve_api/src/serve.py`; constants and parameter definitions are in "
"`serve_api/src/utils/constants.py`."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cdeveloper%5Carchitecture.md:7
msgid "Request lifecycle"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cdeveloper%5Carchitecture.md:9
msgid ""
"sequenceDiagram\n"
"    participant Client\n"
"    participant FastAPI as FastAPI (serve.py)\n"
"    participant KG as Methods KG (rdflib Graph)\n"
"    participant Repo as Publication Repository\n"
"    participant XSLT as lxml XSLT\n"
"\n"
"    Client->>FastAPI: GET /rules/{rule_id_path}\n"
"    FastAPI->>FastAPI: parse rule set ID from path\n"
"    FastAPI->>KG: detect_cprmv_serve_method(rulesetid)\n"
"    KG-->>FastAPI: method config (id formats, URLs, XSLT path)\n"
"\n"
"    alt index == 'latest' or no date\n"
"        FastAPI->>Repo: SRU search (zoekservice.overheid.nl)\n"
"        Repo-->>FastAPI: publication URL + date\n"
"    end\n"
"\n"
"    FastAPI->>Repo: download publication XML\n"
"    Repo-->>FastAPI: XML bytes (temp file)\n"
"    FastAPI->>XSLT: transform XML → CPRMV Turtle\n"
"    XSLT-->>FastAPI: Turtle string\n"
"    FastAPI->>FastAPI: rdflib.parse(turtle)\n"
"    FastAPI->>FastAPI: get_first_rule_by_id_path(graph, path)\n"
"    FastAPI->>FastAPI: get_rule(graph, rule_node) or cbd.serialize()\n"
"    FastAPI-->>Client: response (cprmv-json or RDF)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cdeveloper%5Carchitecture.md:39
msgid "Startup"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cdeveloper%5Carchitecture.md:41
msgid "On startup, `serve.py` calls `set_CPRMVMETHODSKG` twice:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cdeveloper%5Carchitecture.md:43
msgid ""
"`set_CPRMVMETHODSKG(\"./data/cprmvmethods.ttl\", False)` — loads the methods "
"registry fresh into a new graph."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cdeveloper%5Carchitecture.md:44
msgid ""
"`set_CPRMVMETHODSKG(\"./data/cprmv.ttl\", True)` — merges the CPRMV "
"vocabulary into the same graph."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cdeveloper%5Carchitecture.md:46
msgid ""
"The resulting merged graph is stored in "
"`app.cprmvsettings[\"CPRMVMETHODS_KG\"]` and used for all method detection "
"at request time."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cdeveloper%5Carchitecture.md:50
msgid "Method detection"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cdeveloper%5Carchitecture.md:52
msgid ""
"`detect_cprmv_serve_method(cprmvid)` first tries to match the rule set "
"identifier against `cprmvmethods:analysismethods` (the RDF list of BWB, "
"CVDR, CELLAR entries). If no match, it falls back to "
"`cprmvmethods:formalisationmethods` (the DMN 1.3 entry)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cdeveloper%5Carchitecture.md:54
msgid ""
"`detect_cprmv_serve_acknowledged_method(cprmvid, collection)` walks the RDF "
"list and for each method:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cdeveloper%5Carchitecture.md:56
msgid "Reads `cprmv-serve:normalized-id-format` from the methods KG."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cdeveloper%5Carchitecture.md:57
msgid ""
"Calls `normalize_ruleset_id(cprmvid)` to canonicalise shortened IDs (appends "
"`_now_latest` or `_na_latest` for forms without date/index)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cdeveloper%5Carchitecture.md:58
msgid ""
"Uses `parse(normalized_idformat, cprmvid_normalized)` to attempt structural "
"matching."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cdeveloper%5Carchitecture.md:59
msgid ""
"On match, returns a dict of the method's triples plus a `cprmv-"
"serve:id_parts` entry containing the named parse result fields."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cdeveloper%5Carchitecture.md:61
msgid ""
"For `_latest` index forms, a subsequent SRU call "
"(`find_publication_version_valid_on_date`) resolves the actual date and "
"index."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cdeveloper%5Carchitecture.md:65
msgid "Rule graph traversal"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cdeveloper%5Carchitecture.md:67
msgid ""
"`get_first_rule_by_id_path` splits the path by the delimiter and pops the "
"first segment to find root rule nodes via `g.subjects(CPRMV.id, Literal"
"(firstid, lang=\"nl\"))`. It then calls the recursive "
"`get_first_rule_by_Id_path_split_from_rule_as_root`, which:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cdeveloper%5Carchitecture.md:69
msgid "Iterates the `cprmv:hasPart` RDF list of the current rule."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cdeveloper%5Carchitecture.md:70
msgid ""
"Strips non-alphanumeric characters from both the path segment and `g.value"
"(rule, CPRMV.id)`."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cdeveloper%5Carchitecture.md:71
msgid "On match, recurses with the remaining path."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cdeveloper%5Carchitecture.md:72
msgid ""
"If no direct match at this level, still recurses into sub-rules (depth-first "
"skip — intermediate IDs can be omitted)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cdeveloper%5Carchitecture.md:74
msgid ""
"`get_rule(g, rule)` recursively collects all predicate-object pairs for a "
"rule node. For `cprmv:hasPart`, it walks the RDF list and recurses into each "
"item, building a nested dict keyed by `cprmv:id`."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cdeveloper%5Carchitecture.md:78
msgid "Static files"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cdeveloper%5Carchitecture.md:80
msgid ""
"The `/respec/` path is served as a static file directory mounted from "
"`serve_api/respec/`. The ReSpec HTML and assets are included in the Docker "
"image at build time."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cdeveloper%5Carchitecture.md:84
msgid "Locale"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cdeveloper%5Carchitecture.md:86
msgid ""
"The Dockerfile installs `nl_NL.UTF-8` locale, which `serve.py` sets at "
"startup. This is intended to influence the `parse` module's handling of "
"Dutch-formatted strings (e.g. decimal notation), though the practical effect "
"is noted as a TODO in the source."
msgstr ""

