#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cindex.md:1
msgid "CPRMV API"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cindex.md:3
msgid ""
"The **CPRMV API** is a Python/FastAPI service that makes individual rules "
"from Dutch and European legal publications accessible as structured, machine-"
"readable data in real time. It implements the [Core Public Rule Management "
"Vocabulary (CPRMV)]{1} — the RONL standard for expressing and managing "
"public rules across analysis, formalisation, and codification methods."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cindex.md:7
msgid "What it does"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cindex.md:9
msgid ""
"The API accepts a Rule Set identifier (a BWB, CVDR, or EU CELLAR ID) and an "
"optional path of rule identifiers, then:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cindex.md:11
msgid ""
"Resolves the identifier against the appropriate official publication "
"repository."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cindex.md:12
msgid "Downloads the publication XML on-the-fly."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cindex.md:13
msgid "Transforms it to CPRMV using an XSLT stylesheet."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cindex.md:14
msgid "Navigates the resulting rule tree to the requested rule."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cindex.md:15
msgid ""
"Returns the rule in the requested format — `cprmv-json`, Turtle, JSON-LD, or "
"other RDF serialisations."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cindex.md:17
msgid ""
"No pre-loading or batch conversion is required. The API resolves \"latest "
"version valid on a given date\" queries automatically via SRU search of the "
"publication repositories."
msgstr ""

