#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cdefinition-extraction.md:1
msgid "Definition Extraction"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cdefinition-extraction.md:3
msgid ""
"The `unformat` parameter extracts structured values from a rule's "
"`cprmv:definition` text using the Python [`parse`]{1} library's pattern "
"syntax."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cdefinition-extraction.md:7
msgid "When to use it"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cdefinition-extraction.md:9
msgid ""
"Rule definitions in Dutch law frequently embed domain-specific values in "
"natural language:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cdefinition-extraction.md:11
msgid "*Huur: € 1.200,—*"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cdefinition-extraction.md:13
msgid ""
"The `unformat` parameter allows you to pull these values out as named fields "
"in the JSON response, ready for direct use in downstream processing or "
"decision model inputs — without needing a separate text-parsing step."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cdefinition-extraction.md:17
msgid "Pattern syntax"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cdefinition-extraction.md:19
msgid ""
"Use `{fieldname:param_value}` placeholders in the pattern string. The "
"`:param_value` type annotation is required; it matches any non-empty string."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cdefinition-extraction.md:21
msgid "**Pattern:** `{situatie:param_value}: € {norm:param_value}`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cdefinition-extraction.md:23
msgid "This matches a definition like `Huur: € 1.200,—` and extracts:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cdefinition-extraction.md:25
msgid ""
"{\n"
"    \"situatie\": \"Huur\",\n"
"    \"norm\": \"1.200,—\",\n"
"    \"rulesetid\": \"BWBR0015703_2025-07-01_0\",\n"
"    \"rule_id_path\": \"BWBR0015703_2025-07-01_0, Artikel 20, lid 1, "
"onderdeel a.\",\n"
"    \"https://standaarden.open-regels.nl/standards/cprmv/0.4.0/#id\": "
"\"onderdeel a.\",\n"
"    \"https://standaarden.open-regels.nl/standards/cprmv/0.4.0/"
"#definition\": \"Huur: € 1.200,—\"\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cdefinition-extraction.md:36
msgid ""
"The extracted named fields are merged at the top level of the cprmv-json "
"response alongside the full rule predicates and the `rulesetid` and "
"`rule_id_path` context fields."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cdefinition-extraction.md:40
msgid "Behaviour when the pattern does not match"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cdefinition-extraction.md:42
msgid ""
"If the `parse` search does not find the pattern in the definition text, "
"`unformat` has no effect and the standard cprmv-json response is returned "
"without the extracted fields."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cdefinition-extraction.md:46
msgid "Non-breaking spaces"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cdefinition-extraction.md:48
msgid ""
"The API normalises `cprmv:definition` text before matching: sequences of non-"
"breaking spaces (`\\u00A0`) are converted to regular spaces. This ensures "
"patterns work consistently regardless of how the source XML encoded "
"whitespace."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cdefinition-extraction.md:52
msgid "URL encoding the pattern"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cdefinition-extraction.md:54
msgid ""
"The `unformat` value must be URL-encoded in requests constructed manually:"
msgstr ""

